## Option 2: Winston CloudWatch Transport (No Agent)

Direct integration from NestJS to CloudWatch:

```bash
npm install winston winston-cloudwatch @types/winston
```

```typescript
// src/logger-cloudwatch.ts
import { createLogger, format, transports } from 'winston';
import WinstonCloudWatch from 'winston-cloudwatch';

const cloudWatchTransport = new WinstonCloudWatch({
  logGroupName: '/nestjs/travel-maestro',
  logStreamName: () => {
    // Create new stream per day
    return `api-${new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0]}`;
  },
  awsRegion: process.env.AWS_REGION || 'eu-west-1',
  level: 'info',
  jsonMessage: true,
  retentionInDays: 30,
  batchSize: 100,
  handleExceptions: true,
});

export const logger = createLogger({
  level: 'info',
  format: format.combine(
    format.timestamp(),
    format.errors({ stack: true }),
    format.json(),
  ),
  defaultMeta: {
    service: 'travel-maestro-api',
    environment: process.env.NODE_ENV || 'development',
  },
  transports: [
    cloudWatchTransport,
    new transports.Console({
      format: format.combine(format.colorize(), format.simple()),
    }),
  ],
});
```

```typescript
// src/main.ts
import { NestFactory } from '@nestjs/core';
import { AppModule } from './app.module';
import { logger } from './logger-cloudwatch';

async function bootstrap() {
  const app = await NestFactory.create(AppModule, {
    logger: false, // Disable default NestJS logger
  });

  const port = process.env.PORT || 3000;
  await app.listen(port);

  logger.info(`Application started on port ${port}`);
}
bootstrap();
```

**IAM Role for EC2 (direct API):**

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "logs:CreateLogGroup",
        "logs:CreateLogStream",
        "logs:PutLogEvents",
        "logs:DescribeLogStreams"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:logs:*:*:log-group:/nestjs/*"
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## Comparison: EC2 (ASG)

| Aspect | Option 1: Agent | Option 2: Direct |
|--------|-----------------|------------------|
| **Setup** | Agent on EC2 | Winston transport |
| **Performance** | Agent batches, low overhead | Batching in transport |
| **Retries** | Agent handles | Transport handles |
| **Restart needed** | Yes (agent) | No |
| **Best for** | Multiple services logging | Single application |

