# Start CloudWatch Agent
/opt/aws/amazon-cloudwatch-agent/bin/amazon-cloudwatch-agent-ctl \
  -a fetch-config -m ec2 -s -c file:/opt/aws/amazon-cloudwatch-agent/etc/agent.json

# Start application with PM2
npm install -g pm2
pm2 start /home/ec2-user/app/dist/main.js \
  --name "travel-maestro-api" \
  --log /home/ec2-user/app/logs/app.log \
  --time

pm2 startup
pm2 save
```

---

## Summary

| Approach | Command | Best For |
|----------|---------|----------|
| **CloudWatch Agent** | Agent collects stdout | Multiple apps, containers |
| **Winston Direct** | `winston-cloudwatch` | NestJS only, no agent |

**Recommendation:** Use **Option 1 (CloudWatch Agent)** - it's more reliable, handles retries automatically, and works well with ASG since the agent restarts independently of the app.

