cli.content:
Great question! For an **MVP with NestJS**, here's the best-fit approach:

---

## NestJS-Recommended Architecture

NestJS has **built-in conventions** that work perfectly for MVPs:

```
src/
├── common/           # Shared (guards, filters, decorators)
├── config/           # Configuration
├── modules/          # Feature modules
│   ├── projects/
│   │   ├── dto/           # Data transfer objects
│   │   ├── entities/      # Database entities
│   │   ├── projects.controller.ts
│   │   ├── projects.service.ts
│   │   └── projects.module.ts
│   ├── hotels/
│   └── invoices/
├── app.controller.ts
├── app.module.ts
└── main.ts
```

---

## NestJS Patterns That Work for MVP

| Pattern | NestJS Feature | Purpose |
|---------|---------------|---------|
| **Module** | `@Module()` | Organize features |
| **Service** | `@Injectable()` | Business logic |
| **Repository** | TypeORM/Prisma | Data access |
| **Controller** | `@Controller()` | API endpoints |
| **DTO** | `class-validator` | Input validation |
| **Guard** | `@Guard()` | Authentication |
| **Pipe** | `@Pipe()` | Data transformation |

---

## MVP Design Options for NestJS

| Approach | Complexity | Best For |
|----------|------------|----------|
| **Simple Modular** | Low | CRUD-heavy MVPs |
| **DDD-Lite** | Medium | MVPs with business logic |
| **Full DDD** | High | Complex MVPs |

---

## Recommendation: **DDD-Lite for NestJS MVP**

For an MVP, use **DDD concepts where they add value**, not everywhere:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    NESTJS MVP ARCHITECTURE                      │
│                                                                 │
│  MODULES (Bounded Contexts)                                     │
│  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  │
│  │    PROJECTS     │  │     HOTELS      │  │    INVOICES     │  │
│  │                 │  │                 │  │                 │  │
│  │  Controller     │  │  Controller     │  │  Controller     │  │
│  │  Service        │  │  Service        │  │  Service        │  │
│  │  Entity         │  │  Entity         │  │  Entity         │  │
│  │  DTO            │  │  DTO            │  │  DTO            │  │
│  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  │
│                                                                 │
│  COMMON (Shared across all modules)                             │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │  Auth Guards │ Pipes │ Filters │ Decorators │ Utils   │   │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## Why This Works for NestJS MVP

| Factor | Why It Fits |
|--------|-------------|
| **Speed** | NestJS modules are quick to create |
| **Convention** | NestJS expects this structure |
| **Testability** | Services are easily injectable |
| **Refactorable** | Can evolve to full DDD later |
| **Team Onboarding** | Clear, predictable structure |

---

## Example: Simple Project Module

```typescript
// projects/project.entity.ts
@Entity()
export class Project {
  @PrimaryGeneratedColumn()
  id: number;

  @Column()
  name: string;

  @Column({ type: 'enum', enum: ['DRAFT', 'PLANNING', 'COMPLETED'] })
  status: string;
}

// projects/projects.service.ts
@Injectable()
export class ProjectsService {
  constructor(
    @InjectRepository(Project)
    private projectRepo: Repository<Project>,
  ) {}

  async findAll(): Promise<Project[]> {
    return this.projectRepo.find();
  }

  async create(data: CreateProjectDto): Promise<Project> {
    const project = this.projectRepo.create(data);
    return this.projectRepo.save(project);
  }
}

// projects/projects.controller.ts
@Controller('projects')
export class ProjectsController {
  constructor(private readonly projectsService: ProjectsService) {}

  @Get()
  findAll(): Promise<Project[]> {
    return this.projectsService.findAll();
  }

  @Post()
  create(@Body() data: CreateProjectDto): Promise<Project> {
    return this.projectsService.create(data);
  }
}

// projects/projects.module.ts
@Module({
  imports: [TypeOrmModule.forFeature([Project])],
  controllers: [ProjectsController],
  providers: [ProjectsService],
  exports: [ProjectsService],
})
export class ProjectsModule {}
```

---

## Final Answer

| Project Type | Recommended Architecture |
|--------------|-------------------------|
| **MVP + NestJS** | **Modular with DDD-Lite** (our recommendation) |
| Complex MVP + NestJS | Full DDD |
| Simple CRUD MVP | Clean Architecture |

**For your MVP: Use NestJS Modular Architecture with light DDD concepts (entities, services, modules).**

This gives you:
- ✅ Fast development
- ✅ NestJS-native patterns
- ✅ Easy to refactor later
- ✅ Clear structure
- ✅ Scalable to microservices
